---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
import { SPEC_VERSION } from '../../config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="MPP Demo · agents.txt"
  description="Live demonstration of the Machine Payments Protocol (MPP), the session-based companion to x402. The site declares mpp support in agents.json, then a synthetic gated route at /mpp returns a real 402 with a WWW-Authenticate: Payment challenge composed via mppx. The recipient is carried inside the challenge, as the spec requires."
  canonicalUrl="https://agentstxt.dev/demo/mpp"
>
  <!-- Nav -->
  <header class="sticky top-0 z-50 bg-white border-b border-[#e5e5e5]">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 h-14 flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 min-w-0">
        <a href="/" class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold tracking-tight text-[#111] no-underline whitespace-nowrap">
          agents.txt
        </a>
        <span class="text-[#ccc] select-none">/</span>
        <a href="/demo" class="text-sm text-[#555] hover:text-[#111] transition-colors no-underline whitespace-nowrap">Demos</a>
        <span class="text-[#ccc] select-none">/</span>
        <span class="text-sm text-[#111] whitespace-nowrap">MPP</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-x-3 sm:gap-x-5 shrink-0">
        <a href="/spec" class="text-xs text-[#555] hover:text-[#111] transition-colors no-underline">Spec</a>
        <a href="/agents.txt" class="font-mono text-xs text-[#555] hover:text-[#111] transition-colors no-underline">agents.txt</a>
        <a href="/agents.json" class="font-mono text-xs text-[#555] hover:text-[#111] transition-colors no-underline">agents.json</a>
        <a href="/demo" class="text-xs font-medium text-[#111] no-underline border-b border-[#111]">Demo</a>
        <span class="hidden sm:block text-[#ddd] select-none">|</span>
        <a href="https://github.com/agentstxt/agents.txt" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="View on GitHub"
          class="flex text-xs text-[#555] hover:text-[#111] transition-colors no-underline items-center gap-1">
          <svg width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Page body -->
  <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pt-12 pb-24">
    <div class="max-w-[72ch]">

      <!-- Cover -->
      <div class="mb-10 pb-8 border-b border-[#e5e5e5]">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[#111] mb-1">
          MPP (Machine Payments Protocol): Reference
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#777] font-mono mb-6">Session-based · Tempo USDC.e · Stripe SPT (cards, Solana USDC)</p>
        <dl class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm">
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Protocol</dt>
          <dd class="text-[#111]">
            <a href="https://mpp.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="font-mono underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#bbb] hover:decoration-[#111] transition-all">
              mpp.dev
            </a>
          </dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">SDK</dt>
          <dd class="text-[#111]">
            <a href="https://github.com/wevm/mppx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="font-mono underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#bbb] hover:decoration-[#111] transition-all">
              wevm/mppx
            </a>
            <span class="text-[#999]"> (TypeScript)</span>
          </dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Methods</dt>
          <dd class="font-mono text-[#111]">Tempo USDC.e, Stripe SPT</dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Auth scheme</dt>
          <dd class="font-mono text-[#111]">Authorization: Payment</dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Status</dt>
          <dd class="text-[#111]">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center border border-[#111] text-[10px] font-semibold tracking-[0.08em] uppercase px-1.5 py-0.5 leading-none mr-2">Live</span>
            Real announcement read from agents.json. The wire layer probes the dedicated /mpp endpoint (Tempo and/or Stripe via mppx).
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <div class="prose max-w-none mb-10">
        <p>
          The Machine Payments Protocol is the IETF <code>draft-ryan-httpauth-payment</code> scheme co-authored by Stripe and Tempo. MPP is the session-based companion to x402: where x402 attaches a fresh on-chain signature to every request, MPP issues a credential the agent presents in a standard <code>Authorization: Payment</code> header for the duration of a session.
        </p>
        <p>
          A site running MPP through the <code>mppx</code> SDK can register two methods together: Tempo (USDC.e stablecoin on the Tempo chain) and Stripe SPT (the Stripe Payments Token, covering card networks plus Solana USDC). Both methods appear together in a single <code>WWW-Authenticate</code> challenge. The agent picks whichever it can satisfy and authorizes through that path; the server verifies through the same SDK on retry.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs text-[#777] border-l-2 border-[#e5e5e5] pl-3 italic">
          As with x402, the recipient identifier (Tempo wallet, Stripe Business Network profile) is carried in the 402 challenge and never in <code>agents.json</code>. The mppx <code>Challenge.request.recipient</code> field is the canonical location; the same field reaches the agent as part of the <code>WWW-Authenticate: Payment</code> header value.
        </p>

        <h2>Protocol flow</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Step</th><th>Action</th><th>Result</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">0</td><td>Site declares MPP support in <code>agents.json</code></td><td class="text-[#999]"><code>payments.mpp.methods</code> array, no recipient</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">1</td><td>Agent requests a gated resource (no <code>Authorization</code>)</td><td>402 with <code>WWW-Authenticate: Payment</code> challenge carrying the recipient</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-[#ccc]">.</td><td class="text-[#999]">Agent inspects challenge methods, picks Tempo or Stripe, authorizes through the chosen method</td><td class="text-[#999]">SDK-side, not executable in a browser</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-[#ccc]">.</td><td class="text-[#999]">Agent retries with <code>Authorization: Payment &lt;credential&gt;</code>, server verifies via mppx, responds 200</td><td class="text-[#999]">200, <code>Payment-Receipt</code> header</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Demo runner -->
      <div class="border border-[#e5e5e5]">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 border-b border-[#e5e5e5]">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[#111]">Announcement and wire</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[#999] mt-0.5">Live requests, no payment executed</p>
          </div>
          <button
            id="run-btn"
            class="flex items-center gap-2 border border-[#111] text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.06em] uppercase px-4 py-2 hover:bg-[#111] hover:text-white transition-colors disabled:opacity-40 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
          >
            <span id="run-btn-label">Run</span>
          </button>
        </div>

        <div id="steps" class="divide-y divide-[#e5e5e5]">
          {[
            ['0', 'Announcement', 'GET /agents.json, read payments.mpp.methods'],
            ['1', 'Wire',         'GET /mpp  (no Authorization header)  →  expect 402 + WWW-Authenticate: Payment'],
          ].map(([num, label, hint]) => (
            <div class="step" data-step={num} data-state="idle">
              <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-3">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 min-w-0">
                  <span class="step-indicator font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-4">·</span>
                  <div class="min-w-0">
                    <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[#bbb] step-label">{label}</p>
                    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-[#ccc] step-hint mt-0.5">{hint}</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span class="step-badge font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] shrink-0 mt-0.5"></span>
              </div>
              <div class="step-body hidden px-5 pb-4">
                <pre class="step-output bg-[#f6f6f6] border border-[#e5e5e5] text-[11px] font-mono text-[#333] p-4 overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed m-0"></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div id="result-banner" class="hidden px-5 py-4 border-t border-[#e5e5e5]">
          <p id="result-text" class="text-sm font-medium text-[#111]"></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#999] mt-1">To complete the flow, use an mppx-capable agent or the <a href="https://github.com/wevm/mppx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#ccc] hover:decoration-[#999] transition-all">mppx TypeScript SDK</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Method comparison -->
      <div class="prose max-w-none mt-12">
        <h2>Tempo vs Stripe: payment method differences</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th></th><th>Tempo (USDC stablecoin)</th><th>Stripe (cards, Solana USDC)</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Method identifier</td><td class="font-mono text-[11px]">tempo</td><td class="font-mono text-[11px]">stripe</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Settlement layer</td><td>Tempo chain (TIP-20 token transfer)</td><td>Stripe Payments Network (SPT)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Currency</td><td>USDC.e (Tempo mainnet)</td><td>Any Stripe-supported currency, defaults to USD. SPT also covers Solana USDC.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Recipient field</td><td>Tempo wallet address (<code>0x...</code>)</td><td>Stripe Business Network profile ID</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Agent authorization</td><td>Sign and send a TIP-20 transfer through the agent's Tempo wallet</td><td>Authorize a Stripe SPT through a payment method (card, Link, USDC)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Agent secret material</td><td>Tempo wallet private key (held by agent)</td><td>Stripe customer credential (held by agent)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Server verification</td><td><code>mppx.tempo.charge()</code> verifies on-chain transfer</td><td><code>mppx.stripe.charge()</code> verifies SPT through Stripe API</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-medium">Receipt</td><td>Same wire shape: <code>Payment-Receipt</code> header on 200</td><td>Same wire shape: <code>Payment-Receipt</code> header on 200</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>Protocol reference</h2>

        <h3>The 402 challenge: <code>WWW-Authenticate: Payment</code></h3>
        <p>
          When the agent has no <code>Authorization</code> header, the server responds with 402 and a <code>WWW-Authenticate: Payment</code> header containing both supported methods. The challenge value is opaque to the agent except for the method names and a server-assigned challenge identifier; the SDK parses it. The recipient is encoded inside the challenge's <code>request</code> field.
        </p>
        <pre><code>{`HTTP/1.1 402 Payment Required
WWW-Authenticate: Payment
  realm="agents.txt",
  challenge="<server-assigned-challenge-id>",
  methods="tempo,stripe"

{
  "error":   "Payment required",
  "mpp":     { "challenge": "<full-WWW-Authenticate-header-value>" }
}`}</code></pre>

        <h3>Tempo authorization payload</h3>
        <p>
          The agent's Tempo wallet signs and broadcasts a TIP-20 token transfer to the recipient address declared in the challenge. The SDK wraps the resulting transaction proof in a credential and the agent presents it on retry.
        </p>
        <pre><code>{`// Authorization: Payment header value (base64-encoded JSON):
{
  "method":       "tempo",
  "challenge":    "<server-assigned-challenge-id>",
  "amount":       "10000",
  "currency":     "0x20c0000000000000000000000000000000000000",
  "recipient":    "0x<treasury-tempo-address>",
  "transaction":  "0x<tempo-tx-hash>",
  "proof":        { /* TIP-20 transfer proof */ }
}`}</code></pre>

        <h3>Stripe authorization payload</h3>
        <p>
          The agent uses its registered Stripe customer credential to authorize a Stripe Payments Token (SPT). Card networks and Link are supported by default. SPT also covers Solana USDC for agents that prefer paying in stablecoin without operating their own Tempo wallet.
        </p>
        <pre><code>{`// Authorization: Payment header value (base64-encoded JSON):
{
  "method":       "stripe",
  "challenge":    "<server-assigned-challenge-id>",
  "amount":       "1",
  "currency":     "usd",
  "spt":          "<stripe-payments-token>",
  "networkId":    "<stripe-business-network-profile-id>"
}`}</code></pre>

        <h3>Successful response: <code>Payment-Receipt</code></h3>
        <p>
          Verification produces a receipt that the server attaches to the 200 response. The receipt is opaque to the resource handler; mppx generates and signs it. The agent persists the receipt for audit, and may reuse the same <code>Authorization: Payment</code> credential within the session window without renegotiating.
        </p>
        <pre><code>{`HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Payment-Receipt: <base64-encoded-signed-receipt>
Content-Type: application/json

{ "message": "Resource served. Session authorized." }`}</code></pre>

        <h2>Why MPP alongside x402</h2>
        <p>
          The two protocols are complementary, not competitive. x402 is appropriate for fully autonomous agents that hold their own keys and want to settle each request independently on chain. MPP is appropriate for agents that have an existing payment relationship through a custodian (Stripe customer, Tempo wallet manager) and prefer session-based authorization to reduce per-request signing overhead. A site that supports both presents one 402 carrying both an x402 <code>accepts[]</code> body and an MPP <code>WWW-Authenticate</code> header at the same time; the agent picks whichever it speaks.
        </p>
        <p>
          Within MPP, Tempo covers the on-chain stablecoin path while Stripe covers fiat plus Solana USDC. Together they reach the largest possible set of agent wallets and customer profiles without forcing any single chain or rail.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="border-t border-[#e5e5e5] mt-4">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <div class="text-xs text-[#999]">
        <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-[#555]">agents.txt</span>
        {' '}Standard v{SPEC_VERSION} ·{' '}
        <a href="/spec" class="underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#ccc] hover:decoration-[#999] transition-all">Spec</a>
        {' '}·{' '}
        <a href="/demo" class="underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#ccc] hover:decoration-[#999] transition-all">All demos</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-[#bbb]">CC0 (spec) · Apache 2.0 (code). Anyone may implement the standard without restriction.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
function getStep(num: string) {
  return document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(`.step[data-step="${num}"]`)!;
}

function setRunning(num: string) {
  const el = getStep(num);
  el.dataset.state = 'running';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '▸';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-label')!.classList.replace('text-[#bbb]', 'text-[#111]');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-hint')!.classList.replace('text-[#ccc]', 'text-[#777]');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = '...';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.remove('hidden');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = 'Running...';
}

function setDone(num: string, output: string, badge = '') {
  const el = getStep(num);
  el.dataset.state = 'done';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '✓';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.className = 'step-indicator font-mono text-[10px] text-[#111] mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-4';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = badge;
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.className = 'step-badge font-mono text-[10px] text-[#555] shrink-0 mt-0.5';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.remove('hidden');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = output;
}

function setError(num: string, message: string) {
  const el = getStep(num);
  el.dataset.state = 'error';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '✕';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = 'error';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.remove('hidden');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = message;
}

const fmt = (obj: unknown) => JSON.stringify(obj, null, 2);

// Fallback parser when the upstream worker does not duplicate the parsed
// challenges into the JSON body. Mirrors parseMppChallenges in worker.ts:
// splits on the ", Payment " boundary per RFC 7235 multi-challenge form,
// extracts key="value" pairs, base64-decodes the `request` blob into JSON.
function parseChallengesClientSide(headerValue: string): Array<Record<string, unknown>> {
  const pieces = headerValue.split(/,\s*Payment\s+/i);
  pieces[0] = pieces[0].replace(/^Payment\s+/i, '');
  return pieces.map((piece) => {
    const params: Record<string, unknown> = {};
    const re = /(\w+)="([^"]*)"/g;
    let m: RegExpExecArray | null;
    while ((m = re.exec(piece)) !== null) {
      const [, key, value] = m;
      if (key === 'request') {
        try { params.request = JSON.parse(atob(value)); } catch { params.request = value; }
      } else {
        params[key] = value;
      }
    }
    return params;
  });
}

async function run() {
  const btn = document.getElementById('run-btn')!;
  const label = document.getElementById('run-btn-label')!;
  const banner = document.getElementById('result-banner')!;
  const resultText = document.getElementById('result-text')!;

  btn.setAttribute('disabled', '');
  label.textContent = 'Running...';
  banner.classList.add('hidden');
  resultText.className = 'text-sm font-medium text-[#111]';

  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.step').forEach(el => {
    el.dataset.state = 'idle';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '·';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.className = 'step-indicator font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-4';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-label')!.className = 'text-sm font-medium text-[#bbb] step-label';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-hint')!.className = 'font-mono text-[11px] text-[#ccc] step-hint mt-0.5';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = '';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.className = 'step-badge font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] shrink-0 mt-0.5';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.add('hidden');
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = '';
  });

  const origin = window.location.origin;

  try {
    // Step 0: announcement layer (agents.json, payments.mpp)
    setRunning('0');
    const agentsRes = await fetch(`${origin}/agents.json`);
    const agentsJson = await agentsRes.json() as {
      payments?: {
        mpp?:  { methods?: string[]; description?: string };
        x402?: { chains?: string[] };
      };
    };
    const mppDeclared = !!agentsJson.payments?.mpp;
    const methods = agentsJson.payments?.mpp?.methods ?? [];

    const summary = mppDeclared
      ? [
          `MPP declared    yes`,
          `methods         ${methods.length > 0 ? methods.join(', ') : '(none)'}`,
          `session scheme  Authorization: Payment <credential>`,
          ``,
          `Note: the recipient identifier (Tempo wallet, Stripe profile)`,
          `is not in agents.json. Per spec §11.4 it is carried in the`,
          `WWW-Authenticate: Payment challenge on the gated route.`,
        ].join('\n')
      : [
          `MPP declared    no`,
          ``,
          `agents.json does not advertise an MPP block on this deployment.`,
          `Set TREASURY_TEMPO or STRIPE_SECRET_KEY + STRIPE_NETWORK_ID in`,
          `.dev.vars (or environment), then run \`agentify generate --agents\``,
          `to regenerate the announcement. The wire step still runs below.`,
        ].join('\n');

    setDone('0',
      `GET /agents.json, payments.mpp\n\n${summary}\n\nFull response:\n${fmt(agentsJson)}`,
      mppDeclared ? `${methods.length} method${methods.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''}` : 'not declared',
    );

    // Step 1: wire layer (probe /mpp for WWW-Authenticate: Payment)
    setRunning('1');
    const probeRes = await fetch(`${origin}/mpp`);
    const wwwAuth = probeRes.headers.get('WWW-Authenticate');
    let probeBody: unknown = null;
    try { probeBody = await probeRes.json(); } catch { /* not JSON */ }

    const mppHeader = wwwAuth && /^Payment\b/i.test(wwwAuth) ? wwwAuth : null;
    const probeError = (probeBody && typeof probeBody === 'object' && 'error' in (probeBody as Record<string, unknown>))
      ? (probeBody as { error?: string }).error
      : undefined;
    const probeMessage = (probeBody && typeof probeBody === 'object' && 'message' in (probeBody as Record<string, unknown>))
      ? (probeBody as { message?: string }).message
      : undefined;
    const inactive   = probeRes.status === 503 && probeError === 'endpoint_inactive';
    const runtimeErr = probeRes.status === 503 && probeError === 'mpp_runtime_error';

    if (mppHeader) {
      // Prefer the parsed array the worker emits in mpp.challenges; fall back
      // to a client-side parse of the header value when the body shape differs
      // (e.g. another mppx-backed server that does not duplicate the challenges
      // into the body).
      const bodyChallenges = (probeBody && typeof probeBody === 'object' && 'mpp' in (probeBody as Record<string, unknown>))
        ? ((probeBody as { mpp?: { challenges?: Array<Record<string, unknown>> } }).mpp?.challenges)
        : undefined;
      const challenges = (bodyChallenges && bodyChallenges.length > 0)
        ? bodyChallenges
        : parseChallengesClientSide(mppHeader);

      const blocks = challenges.map((ch, i) => {
        const lines = [
          `  ── challenge ${i + 1} of ${challenges.length} ──`,
          `  method        ${ch.method ?? '(none)'}`,
          `  id            ${ch.id ?? '(none)'}`,
          `  realm         ${ch.realm ?? '(none)'}`,
          `  intent        ${ch.intent ?? '(none)'}`,
        ];
        if (ch.description) lines.push(`  description   ${ch.description}`);
        if (ch.expires)     lines.push(`  expires       ${ch.expires}`);
        lines.push(``);
        lines.push(`  request (base64-decoded):`);
        const reqStr = (typeof ch.request === 'object' && ch.request !== null)
          ? fmt(ch.request).split('\n').map((l) => `    ${l}`).join('\n')
          : `    ${ch.request ?? '(none)'}`;
        lines.push(reqStr);
        return lines.join('\n');
      }).join('\n\n');

      setDone('1',
        [
          `GET /mpp  (no Authorization header)`,
          ``,
          `Status  ${probeRes.status} Payment Required`,
          ``,
          `${challenges.length} challenge${challenges.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''} in the WWW-Authenticate header (RFC 7235 multi-scheme form):`,
          ``,
          blocks,
          ``,
          `An mppx-capable agent parses methods, picks one it can satisfy,`,
          `authorizes through it, then retries with:`,
          `  Authorization: Payment <base64-credential>`,
        ].join('\n'),
        `${probeRes.status} · ${challenges.length} method${challenges.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''}`,
      );
      resultText.textContent = mppDeclared
        ? `MPP challenge${challenges.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''} received. The announcement (agents.json) and the wire (WWW-Authenticate header) agree. An mppx-capable agent picks one of the methods above and authorizes through it.`
        : `MPP challenge present on the wire but no payments.mpp block in agents.json. Either declare it (regenerate after setting MPP credentials) or the wire layer is misconfigured.`;
    } else if (inactive) {
      setDone('1',
        [
          `GET /mpp`,
          ``,
          `Status  503 Service Unavailable`,
          ``,
          `The /mpp demo route is offline on this deployment.`,
          `No MPP credentials configured on the worker.`,
          ``,
          `Set TREASURY_TEMPO (Tempo) and/or STRIPE_SECRET_KEY + STRIPE_NETWORK_ID (Stripe)`,
          `in .dev.vars and restart dev. The agents.json mpp block reads the same env vars`,
          `via agentify, so announcement and wire activate together.`,
        ].join('\n'),
        '503 inactive',
      );
      resultText.textContent = `MPP wire offline on this deployment. The announcement step is the spec-mandated declaration; the wire step needs MPP credentials in .dev.vars (TREASURY_TEMPO and/or Stripe pair).`;
    } else if (runtimeErr) {
      setDone('1',
        [
          `GET /mpp`,
          ``,
          `Status  503 Service Unavailable`,
          ``,
          `mppx threw at request time. The worker caught it and returned a clean 503`,
          `(rather than crashing). Most common causes: an SDK signature mismatch`,
          `between worker.ts and the installed mppx version, an invalid currency or`,
          `decimals on a charge config, or a Stripe SDK call hitting an invalid key.`,
          ``,
          `Underlying error:`,
          probeMessage ?? '(none)',
        ].join('\n'),
        '503 runtime error',
      );
      resultText.textContent = `mppx errored at request time. The error message above identifies the failing field or call. The announcement step is unaffected; only the wire step failed.`;
    } else {
      setDone('1',
        [
          `GET /mpp  (no Authorization header)`,
          ``,
          `Status  ${probeRes.status} ${probeRes.statusText}`,
          ``,
          `No WWW-Authenticate: Payment header in the response.`,
          `The /mpp route accepted the request but did not emit an MPP challenge.`,
          `This usually means an mppx configuration issue; check the worker logs.`,
          ``,
          `Response body:`,
          fmt(probeBody),
        ].join('\n'),
        `${probeRes.status} · no challenge`,
      );
      resultText.textContent = `Wire layer returned an unexpected response. Check worker logs.`;
    }
    banner.classList.remove('hidden');

  } catch (err) {
    const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
    const running = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step[data-state="running"]');
    if (running) setError(running.dataset.step!, msg);
    resultText.textContent = 'Flow interrupted. See step above for details.';
    resultText.classList.add('text-[#c00]');
    banner.classList.remove('hidden');
  } finally {
    btn.removeAttribute('disabled');
    label.textContent = 'Run again';
  }
}

document.getElementById('run-btn')!.addEventListener('click', run);
</script>
